metadata.name: Paesaggio #28
metadata.description:
In this work I used the tools I learned in developing precedent works to generate a landscape with hills, flowers, streams, ruins, sky and clouds. The generated landscape gives the impression of a natural one but at the same time it has some "abstract" traits that reveal the geometrical properties of the noise generation process. This noise is used both for the morphological aspect and for colors assignment.

Developed with p5.js using WEBGL renderer.
Rendering is faster with chrome browser.

[s] to save a 1600x1600 png.


Features:
"Palette": 12 colormap
"Sky":  Day, Night, Gray - 15% Gray, 20% Night, 65% Day
"Ruins": True, False - 33% True
"Streams": True, False - 33% True
"Flower": Red-Blue, Fuchsia-Yellow, Rose-Violet
"Border": True, False - 25% True


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Stuck Inside #43
metadata.description:
As Spring transitions to Summer, flowers are in full bloom. With no outside view from my desk, I find myself daydreaming of walks around the yard, watering flowers, and watching the insects.

This is a simple and abstract kinetic piece that represents the daydreams I have while working, as I look forward to my next break, when I can walk outside for a few minutes.

100% of secondary sale royalties will go to the Processing Foundation.

The piece is responsive and will adapt to your browser window size. Press SPACE to export a high-resolution PNG image of the current frame at the current aspect ratio. 

If you are using Safari, the animation will be rate limited until you click or tap once on the piece.

metadata.name: Desert Solitude #122
metadata.description: "Desert Solitude" is an exploration of my love for crystals, architecture, being one with nature, escaping technology and becoming ok with the idea of being alone. The series was derived using diffusion Ai models and put together in a generative image composition on fx(hash) May 2022. 123 editions were made available.

metadata.name: Boids 2D #70
metadata.description:
'Boids 2D' is a Generative Token that represent the flocking of birds over a landscape. The name 'Boids' comes from a famous computer animation / simulation program.

The landscape is rendered as a texture using a kind of warped noise as height map.

The boids are disposed along the flow lines obtained from the noise gradient. This gives the sensation that the Boids follow the undulations of the landscape.

Previously embedded in the 'Boids' (3D) Generative Token as an ester egg on 20% of iterations, now every iterations will be 2D as viewed from the sky.

Every owner of the 'Boids' (3D) GT will receive one 'Boids 2D' for free. The owner that minted a 'Boids' with ester egg will receive two 'Boids 2D' for free.

It is possible to save a 1600x1600 png with key 's'.

Sources of variations are:
- Noise warping control parameters generating different grade of complexity and different shape an the landscape and Boids flock (combined on a single number on the features).
- 21 color mapping for landscape and Boids.
- Two kind of border, solid or negative.

Features:
Palette: color palette name (21 different palettes)
NoiseControl: noise control parameter (0 - 15)
Border: the border can be in solid color or negative color (Solid, Negative)


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Alienpillars #168
metadata.description:
"A rare type of bug that supposedly arrived on a cargo ship is destroying crops on planet Uctumi, in the binary system of Extronium. A wide variety of very resistant subspecies has mutated and it is necessary to study and identify all of them to obtain a gen-activated pesticide that will work on all of their variations. The pest department of the Uctumi central government is working hard on it, and they say that these strange critters are probably related to similar species that inhabited the planet Earth of the Solar system a long time ago and have spread over the galaxy."

My second piece using the p5.js raymarcher I wrote. The drawing is made of circles and lines based on the 3D data. I wanted to try something hairy as it's easy to draw lines aligned to the surface normal with this method. I also used a shader for the frame and the glitchy/sketch features.

Features 

body color: green-red-purple-yellow-blue-black
body tone: dark-light
spots color: orange-green-blue-yellow-white
hair tips: yes-no
hair #1: short-medium-long
hair #2: short-medium-long
head size: small-medium-large
head shape: long-spherical-wide
glitchy mode: 10% chance
sketch mode: 9% chance

metadata.name: Rings #21
metadata.description:
Rings is the cummulative texturized generative artwork obtained after several animations of a determinated number of particles seeking a concentric pattern in several rings. But in this case, to get some different results of depth and texture, the chosen particles weregeometrical 2D shapes (like lines, circles, squares and triangles). Also, white 1D dots with low stroke in a descentralized radius from pattern center brings a nice highlighting effect, helping the depth feeling.
All the codes were developed and studyed for a quite time, and after a high number of tests and modifications I believe Rings is ready to be yours!

Its a big pleasure be back :)

And again....palletes carefully chosen.

See the features! Ranking system set up!

Press 's' to save canvas.
Nice experience at full view.

metadata.name: Ornithic #166
metadata.description:
Pure p5.js code. No svg, no image, no other materials. Creating code arts with polar coordinate system and algorithms are my passion. This generative art contains a lot of features that may be rare than common.  

‚Ä¢ 30 color palettes // 2 of them have 3 different colors
‚Ä¢ 4 grass structures // With the same algorithm 
‚Ä¢ 16 flower types //  Count, leaf number and size
‚Ä¢ 6 color functions // Different colorizations with b&w 

Also, the outputs of the project are very high resolution to print or something like that.
April / 2022
Rhaegar

metadata.name: In the Edge #437
metadata.description:
./ In the Edge

It's been a long time since your journey began, caring for the ones you love, pursuing your dreams, and giving the best of you. 

Now you know you can't go back, you can't go further, you know your time is coming.

How far did you go? It doesn't matter, you did it right. Your accomplishments will serve well the next generations in their journeys, in their search for themselves.

Now it's time to stop, time to take a moment and contemplate the vast universe.

Soon all of this will be ending.

You did it right.

Embrace the void.
=========
=========


./ Color scheme (feature)
There are 12 color schemes and with each set, specific arrays for color collections for the space, stars, planet, and accent colors. 

These are color schemes in the known universe of "In the Edge":
- Mars visions
- Cyberpunk
- Unknown passenger 
- Renegade
- Primary
- Coral
- r.e.d.
- Machines of an ancient-future 
- The void
- Tinted light 
- Malibu dreams
- Atari (horrendous brown, red and yellowish combinations... I love it)

./ Mountain type (feature)
In the Edge, you will find a mountain, and that mountain will be special, which type will you find?

- Parallela insolitum
- Sandy dunes of the truth
- Wavy uncertainty
- Intrinsic soul ridges
- Cerritulus formationis

./ Mountain direction (feature)
Life is about direction... mountains too.

- Left
- Right
- Left-Right

./ Space scenery
This is the spicy touch, some of the iterations will have animation and others will not, giving you a clear view of the magnificent space in front of you.

- Clean (NOT animated)
- Windy planet (animated)
- Topographic planet (animated)
- Meteor shower (animated)

./ Distance from Earth (feature)
How far did you go? Your travel could be from 1 lightyear to 999,999,999 lightyears (that's a lot of lights and years!). However just a few will pass the barrier of 99,999,999ly.

// Additional perks
./ Planet names 
Planet names are unique and they are conformed by three blocks.

The first block is a conjunction between ancient Latin names and Japanese last names. 

The second block takes the last three characters from the fxhash.

The third block takes three numbers from the number seed obtained from fxrand().

The planet you land will be unique, as unique as you are.

// Controls
./ Pause-Play animation
Because maybe (and just maybe) you want to freeze the perfect moment before closing your eyes.

[Backspace] Pause.
[Enter] Play

Applies to "Space scenery" features windy planet, topographic planet, and meteor shower.

metadata.name: Linguistic #40
metadata.description:
Linguistic is an abstract geometric artwork that explores geometric figures in a minimal way. The power in this work comes essentially from texture, color, form, and a vectorized painting with thin lines. These painted lines bring an idea of visual communication, an invitation to see words as symbols, to think of the many different alphabets and ways of sharing thoughts. From prehistoric cave paintings to Nazca lines, from Devanagari to Arabic. Or just the unconsciously feeling transmitted by art.

This is a tribute to the 100 years of Brasil‚Äôs modern art week from 1922.

made with p5js

metadata.name: Room of Imagination #30
metadata.description:
"Is this the real life?

Is this just fantasy?"

Room of Imagination is an exercise of fantasy, where a room of our creative mind comes true.

The colors and elements convey sensations and the final result conveys the feeling.


The Rooms of Imagination are layered artworks generated from a pool of previously rendered digital furniture.
